 I'm not going anywhere.

1004
00:45:05,380 --> 00:45:07,411
This is almost like being on vacation.

1005
00:45:07,411 --> 00:45:08,764
 [CHUCKLES] Well, good.

1006
00:45:11,470 --> 00:45:14,190
That's all I want to say.

1007
00:45:14,190 --> 00:45:15,250
 Why did you say you like me?

1008
00:45:19,860 --> 00:45:21,360
 I don't know.

1009
00:45:21,360 --> 00:45:22,990
It just slipped out.

1010
00:45:22,990 --> 00:45:24,540
 It struck me kind of strange.

1011
00:45:30,564 --> 00:45:33,440
 Did it?

1012
00:45:33,440 --> 00:45:34,792
 It was nice.

1013
00:45:34,792 --> 00:45:37,070
It meant something to me.

1014
00:45:37,070 --> 00:45:38,530
I didn't expect it to.

1015
00:45:41,857 --> 00:45:43,390
 Well, I think you better listener to Rowena.

1016
00:45:43,390 --> 00:45:44,664
She knows me like a book.

1017
00:45:49,020 --> 00:45:50,472
Well, goodnight.

1018
00:45:54,360 --> 00:45:57,790
I'm gonna be just on the other side of the hall, you know,

