00:58:21,860 --> 00:58:24,740
[BIRDSONG]

1349
00:58:24,740 --> 00:58:27,140
[CAR APPROACHING]

1350
00:58:28,580 --> 00:58:30,900
 I wouldn't pick us up on a bet.

1351
00:58:30,900 --> 00:58:32,780
[BIRDSONG]

1352
00:58:35,080 --> 00:58:36,220
 Ha-ha.

1353
00:58:36,220 --> 00:58:39,810
Look at this, just as I thought.

1354
00:58:39,810 --> 00:58:41,720
 Shaw, you are brilliant.

1355
00:58:41,720 --> 00:58:43,710
Too bad they'll probably be in the next state

1356
00:58:43,710 --> 00:58:46,504
before we get out of here.

1357
00:58:46,504 --> 00:58:47,496
WOMAN: Bye, now.

1358
00:58:54,500 --> 00:58:55,400
 Thank you.

1359
00:58:55,400 --> 00:58:58,750
MAN: You betcha.

1360
00:58:58,750 --> 00:58:59,650
 Give me those.

1361
00:58:59,650 --> 00:59:00,550
That's it.

1362
00:59:04,490 --> 00:59:05,730
There you go.

1363
00:59:05,730 --> 00:59:07,080
 Blind leading the blind, Walter.

1364
00:59:07,080 --> 00:59:10,100
 Honey, we are in a lot better shape than you think we are.

1365
00:59:10,100 --> 00:59:12,900
Now, get yourself some coffee, some donuts,

1366
00:59:12,900 --> 00:59:14,595
and I will be back in a flash. - Walter.

1367
00:59:14,595 --> 00:59:15,585
 Come on.

1368
00:59:32,450 --> 00:59:34,762
WOMAN (ON SPEAKER): Service department, line three.

1369
00:59:34,762 --> 00:59:37,227
 Hi.

1370
00:59:37,227 --> 00:59:40,680
[PHONE RINGING IN DISTANCE]

1371
00:59:40,680 --> 00:59:41,977
- May I help you? - No.

1372
00:59:41,977 --> 00:59:42,600
No. I'm just looking.

1373
00:59:42,600 --> 00:59:43,800
Thank you very much. - All right.

1374
00:59:43,800 --> 00:59:44,930
- This is nice. - Very nice.

1375
00:59:49,380 --> 00:59:50,990
WALTER: Don't you work too hard.

1376
00:59:50,990 --> 00:59:52,478
WOMAN: I won't.

1377
00:59:52,478 --> 00:59:55,454
[WOMEN LAUGHING]

1378
01:00:13,310 --> 01:00:14,495
 Yes, sir.

1379
01:00:14,495 --> 01:00:15,395
 Oh, hi.

1380
01:00:15,395 --> 01:00:16,340
Uh, I just got to call.

1381
01:00:16,340 --> 01:00:17,380
My new Thunderbird's ready.

1382
01:00:17,380 --> 01:00:18,280
 Name?

1383
01:00:18,280 --> 01:00:19,324
 Charleston-- John Charleston.

1384
01:00:19,324 --> 01:00:21,390
Eh, actually, it might say Jack because my wife brought it in.

1385
01:00:25,800 --> 01:00:26,700
 Yes, sir.

1386
01:00:26,700 --> 01:00:27,780
She's all done now.

1387
01:00:27,780 --> 01:00:28,680
He's at the cashier.

1388
01:00:28,680 --> 01:00:30,499
- Great, what's the damage? - No charge.

1389
01:00:30,499 --> 01:00:31,454
It's all under warranty.

1390
01:00:31,454 --> 01:00:32,920
 Well, that about makes my day, doesn't it?

1391
01:00:32,920 --> 01:00:34,230
[LAUGHS] Thank you very much.

1392
01:00:34,230 --> 01:00:35,700
You know it is good doing business

1393
01:00:35,700 --> 01:00:36,690
in a place you can trust.

1394
01:00:40,618 --> 01:00:42,582
[HORN HONKING]

1395
01:00:45,530 --> 01:00:47,792
Hey, Bunny Brown!

1396
01:00:47,792 --> 01:00:49,730
Hoo-hee!

1397
01:00:49,730 --> 01:00:53,010
Now, is this more your style, air conditioning,

1398
01:00:53,010 --> 01:00:54,250
quadraphonic sound.

1399
01:00:54,250 --> 01:00:56,183
Anything you want, it's got it. Come on.

1400
01:00:56,183 --> 01:00:57,598
Hop on in.

1401
01:00:57,598 --> 01:01:00,592
[BIRDSONG]

1402
01:01:13,580 --> 01:01:15,530
Next I'm gonna buy you a new dress, honey.

1403
01:01:15,530 --> 01:01:17,170
Hey, Rowena gave me a couple hundred bucks.

1404
01:01:17,170 --> 01:01:19,260
We got to look sharp for business.

1405
01:01:19,260 --> 01:01:21,826
Smile, Bunny.

1406
01:01:21,826 --> 01:01:22,804
We're doing fine.

1407
01:01:31,606 --> 01:01:34,540
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

1408
01:01:35,518 --> 01:01:36,496
[BELL RINGS]

1409
01:01:36,496 --> 01:01:37,510
 Good evening, folks.

1410
01:01:37,510 --> 01:01:38,410
 How are you doing?

1411
01:01:38,410 --> 01:01:40,090
A room for two, please--

1412
01:01:40,090 --> 01:01:41,230
honeymoon suite, if you got it.

1413
01:01:41,230 --> 01:01:42,350
 Just married?

1414
01:01:42,350 --> 01:01:43,400
 Well, the second time around.

1415
01:01:43,400 --> 01:01:45,500
 [CHUCKLES] Well, you can't expect to get it right

1416
01:01:45,500 --> 01:01:46,580
without a little practice.

1417
01:01:46,580 --> 01:01:47,480
 Uh-uh.

1418
01:01:47,480 --> 01:01:49,775
Practice makes perfect, doesn't it?

1419
01:01:49,775 --> 01:01:51,680
[CHUCKLES]

1420
01:01:51,680 --> 01:01:52,730
 Well, Mr. And Mrs. Uh--

1421
01:01:52,730 --> 01:01:53,630
 Charleston.

1422
01:01:53,630 --> 01:01:56,200
 --Charleston, that room happens to be on special.

1423
01:01:56,200 --> 01:01:57,770
 Don't care what it costs. Don't even tell me.

1424
01:01:57,770 --> 01:01:59,150
Just surprise me on Tuesday morning.

1425
01:01:59,150 --> 01:02:01,230
- Oh, paying with a credit card? - Uh-uh.

1426
01:02:01,230 --> 01:02:02,390
I'm a cash-only man--

1427
01:02:02,390 --> 01:02:03,720
first thing Tuesday morning.

1428
01:02:03,720 --> 01:02:05,600
By the way, brother, if you have a screwdriver,

1429
01:02:05,600 --> 01:02:07,820
I'd like to borrow it to fix the license plate

1430
01:02:07,820 --> 01:02:08,770
of my brand new Thunderbird.

1431
01:02:08,770 --> 01:02:10,013
See it out there?

1432
01:02:10,013 --> 01:02:12,320
[CHUCKLES] Isn't that a dandy?

1433
01:02:12,320 --> 01:02:15,610
 Well, uh, we have a cash-in--advance policy.

1434
01:02:15,610 --> 01:02:18,180
 Oh, well, why didn't you tell me?

1435
01:02:18,180 --> 01:02:20,820
This might take care of one night,

1436
01:02:20,820 --> 01:02:23,611
in case we change our minds.

1437
01:02:23,611 --> 01:02:25,310
 Um, I was about to say we'll make

1438
01:02:25,310 --> 01:02:27,170
an exception for you folks.

1439
01:02:27,170 --> 01:02:28,870
Tuesday's just fine.

1440
01:02:28,870 --> 01:02:30,220
 You sure now?

1441
01:02:30,220 --> 01:02:31,120
Thank you very kindly.

1442
01:02:31,120 --> 01:02:32,878
Have a good night.

1443
01:02:36,336 --> 01:02:45,730
[DOOR CLOSES]

1444
01:02:45,730 --> 01:02:48,120
Why don't you, uh, just stand by that post there,

1445
01:02:48,120 --> 01:02:50,570
honey, for a second just enough to block the old boy's view.

1446
01:02:53,920 --> 01:02:55,970
 You are the most unprincipled man I ever met.

1447
01:02:55,970 --> 01:02:57,560
I don't know why I even like you.

1448
01:03:08,730 --> 01:03:12,900
 This mattress is as hard as tin!

1449
01:03:12,900 --> 01:03:13,900
My back aches.

1450
01:03:13,900 --> 01:03:15,580
My nose is broken.

1451
01:03:15,580 --> 01:03:18,680
You're just too damn rough and tumble for me, Bunny.

1452
01:03:18,680 --> 01:03:20,520
 Let me sleep, Walter.

1453
01:03:20,520 --> 01:03:25,210
 [CHUCKLES] (SINGING) I'm going down to Florida

1454
01:03:25,210 --> 01:03:29,320
to get some sand in my shoes.

1455
01:03:29,320 --> 01:03:32,470
Oh, yes, I'm going down to Florida

1456
01:03:32,470 --> 01:03:37,000
to get some sand in my shoes.

1457
01:03:37,000 --> 01:03:41,352
Take the Orange Blossom Special and lose these New York blues.

1458
01:03:41,352 --> 01:03:42,847
[TOILET FLUSHES]

1459
01:03:43,747 --> 01:03:44,705
Woo-ooh-woo-ooh.

1460
01:03:44,705 --> 01:03:47,740
Woo-ooh-woo-ooh. (SPEAKING) Come on, Bunny.

1461
01:03:47,740 --> 01:03:49,735
[CLAPPING] Today's the day.

1462
01:03:49,735 --> 01:03:52,026
Come on, we got plans to make.

1463
01:03:52,026 --> 01:03:53,845
 Walter Sharphorn never plans.

1464
01:03:53,845 --> 01:03:55,350
 Hey, this is serious.

1465
01:03:55,350 --> 01:03:56,280
Now, here's what I think.

1466
01:03:56,280 --> 01:03:57,180
Come on, wake up.

1467
01:03:57,180 --> 01:03:58,660
[CLAPS] Wake up.

1468
01:03:58,660 --> 01:04:00,780
We have Archie coming along, right?

1469
01:04:00,780 --> 01:04:02,020
He's got the money in a suitcase.

1470
01:04:02,020 --> 01:04:04,590
And he sets it down someplace where we can see him from up

1471
01:04:04,590 --> 01:04:05,940
so we can watch for cops.

1472
01:04:05,940 --> 01:04:08,910
I think we get a-- a room in some hotel downtown.

1473
01:04:08,910 --> 01:04:11,350
Then the second he leaves, [CLAPS] we jump on it,

1474
01:04:11,350 --> 01:04:12,870
beat it out of there.

1475
01:04:12,870 --> 01:04:15,280
I think I want it all in 20s, too.

1476
01:04:15,280 --> 01:04:16,750
 You'll need three suitcases.

1477
01:04:16,750 --> 01:04:18,452
It'll have to be 100s.

1478
01:04:18,452 --> 01:04:20,080
 Ooh, I hadn't thought of that.

1479
01:04:20,080 --> 01:04:22,603
It is about a wagon load full of money, ain't it?

1480
01:04:22,603 --> 01:04:23,503
Oh, man.

1481
01:04:23,503 --> 01:04:25,230
[CHUCKLES]

1482
01:04:25,230 --> 01:04:28,380
 I think he ought to put it in a black double trash bag,

1483
01:04:28,380 --> 01:04:30,790
leave it in an alley someplace near the trash

1484
01:04:30,790 --> 01:04:32,760
can so it won't look out of place,

1485
01:04:32,760 --> 01:04:34,926
tie it with a red ribbon.

1486
01:04:34,926 --> 01:04:37,494
WALTER: Oh, yeah, so we can tell it from other trash.

1487
01:04:37,494 --> 01:04:39,838
BUNNY: And I think we ought to pay some bum to come and pick

1488
01:04:39,838 --> 01:04:40,890
it up and bring it to us.

1489
01:04:40,890 --> 01:04:45,050
And that way if Archie pulls something, they won't catch us.

1490
01:04:45,050 --> 01:04:46,500
 That's real good.

1491
01:04:46,500 --> 01:04:48,500
But when did you have time to think of all that?

1492
01:04:48,500 --> 01:04:49,915
 I read it one time in a book.

1493
01:04:49,915 --> 01:04:50,920
 Oh. Huh.

1494
01:04:50,920 --> 01:04:51,820
OK.

1495
01:04:51,820 --> 01:04:54,330
I thought it sounded pretty planned out.

1496
01:04:54,330 --> 01:04:55,990
You're all right, Bunny.

1497
01:04:55,990 --> 01:04:57,420
You're smarter than you look.

1498
01:05:04,392 --> 01:05:07,878
Mm-mm-mm-mm.

1499
01:05:07,878 --> 01:05:10,368
[PHONE DIALLING]

1500
01:05:10,368 --> 01:05:12,858
[PHONE RINGING]

1501
01:05:12,858 --> 01:05:15,846
[PHONE RINGS]

1502
01:05:16,880 --> 01:05:19,290
 Brown residence?

1503
01:05:19,290 --> 01:05:22,662
WALTER: Uh, Archie Brown, please.

1504
01:05:22,662 --> 01:05:26,040
[ORGAN PLAYS "WEDDING MARCH"]

1505
01:05:26,040 --> 01:05:28,120
 I'm afraid he's busy right now.

1506
01:05:28,120 --> 01:05:29,780
 Look, you tell him it's an emergency.

1507
01:05:29,780 --> 01:05:30,680
Get in here.

1508
01:05:33,010 --> 01:05:34,480
 What's the matter?

1509
01:05:34,480 --> 01:05:36,940
[ORGAN PLAYING]

1510
01:05:36,940 --> 01:05:39,320
 Emergency call, sir.

1511
01:05:39,320 --> 01:05:40,890
 Hello?

1512
01:05:40,890 --> 01:05:41,790
WALTER: Archie?

1513
01:05:41,790 --> 01:05:43,380
 No, but he's busy.

1514
01:05:43,380 --> 01:05:45,230
Call back later.

1515
01:05:45,230 --> 01:05:46,130
 What the hell's going on?

1516
01:05:46,130 --> 01:05:47,170
 (WHISPERS) My son.

1517
01:05:47,170 --> 01:05:48,270
 Wait a minute, dipstick.

1518
01:05:48,270 --> 01:05:49,520
You tell him it's an emergency.

1519
01:05:49,520 --> 01:05:50,735
Tell him it's about your mother.

1520
01:05:50,735 --> 01:05:52,290
 Hey, look, this is Joe Brown.

1521
01:05:52,290 --> 01:05:53,410
Who the hell's this?

1522
01:05:53,410 --> 01:05:55,380
 Look, I want to talk to your father.

1523
01:05:55,380 --> 01:05:57,900
You have exactly 30 seconds, moron.

1524
01:05:57,900 --> 01:05:59,910
Now get him!

1525
01:05:59,910 --> 01:06:01,310
[ORGAN PLAYING]

1526
01:06:01,310 --> 01:06:02,210
 I don't believe it.

1527
01:06:02,210 --> 01:06:04,643
They're having the wedding!

1528
01:06:04,643 --> 01:06:06,415
I'm not there, and they're having the [HORN BEEPING]

1529
01:06:06,415 --> 01:06:07,350
damn wedding!

1530
01:06:07,350 --> 01:06:08,950
 For Pete's sake, Bunny, I got enough problems.

1531
01:06:08,950 --> 01:06:10,227
That kid of yours is a real dink.

1532
01:06:10,227 --> 01:06:11,127
 They're all dinks!

1533
01:06:11,127 --> 01:06:13,750
God, I am kidnapped, and they're having

1534
01:06:13,750 --> 01:06:15,274
champagne and wedding cake. - Shh!

1535
01:06:15,274 --> 01:06:16,740
They don't even know you're being kidnapped.

1536
01:06:16,740 --> 01:06:17,930
PASTOR: Dear friends--

1537
01:06:17,930 --> 01:06:18,830
 Dad!

1538
01:06:18,830 --> 01:06:21,061
PASTOR: We have gathered here in the presence of God

1539
01:06:21,061 --> 01:06:23,160
to join Lionel-- [WHISTLE]

1540
01:06:23,160 --> 01:06:24,480
 Dad! Come here.

1541
01:06:24,480 --> 01:06:25,380
Come here.

1542
01:06:25,380 --> 01:06:27,420
The phone is for you.

1543
01:06:27,420 --> 01:06:28,580
It's important.

1544
01:06:28,580 --> 01:06:31,102
 Ah, would you hold on just one moment, please?

1545
01:06:31,102 --> 01:06:32,566
[CROWD MURMURING]

1546
01:06:32,566 --> 01:06:33,466
Play.

1547
01:06:33,466 --> 01:06:35,100
Play-- anything.

1548
01:06:35,100 --> 01:06:36,000
[ORGAN PLAYING]

1549
01:06:36,000 --> 01:06:37,474
 He's coming.

1550
01:06:37,474 --> 01:06:40,060
[CROWD MURMURING]

1551
01:06:40,060 --> 01:06:41,310
 Yeah, hello? This is Archie Brown.

1552
01:06:41,310 --> 01:06:42,520
Who the hell is this?

1553
01:06:42,520 --> 01:06:44,380
 Look, you're pressing your luck, Archie.

1554
01:06:44,380 --> 01:06:45,490
Don't be a wise guy.

1555
01:06:45,490 --> 01:06:46,480
Don't act tough.

1556
01:06:46,480 --> 01:06:47,734
Just listen.

1557
01:06:47,734 --> 01:06:48,700
Now, your wife is my hostage.

1558
01:06:48,700 --> 01:06:51,090
And if you ever want to see her in one piece,

1559
01:06:51,090 --> 01:06:54,370
take a big, black double garbage bag, fill it with $100 bills,

1560
01:06:54,370 --> 01:06:57,040
50 to a packet, then tie it up with a red ribbon.

1561
01:06:57,040 --> 01:06:58,961
I'll call you Monday noon and tell you where to drop it.

1562
01:06:58,961 --> 01:07:01,688
 Bunny's kidnapped? [CROWD GASPS]

1563
01:07:01,688 --> 01:07:03,520
WALTER: [INAUDIBLE] you're catching on.

1564
01:07:03,520 --> 01:07:05,530
 Well, how much do you want?

1565
01:07:05,530 --> 01:07:06,430
 Half a million.

1566
01:07:06,430 --> 01:07:08,270
 Are you out of your mind?

1567
01:07:08,270 --> 01:07:10,660
I don't have that kind of money.

1568
01:07:10,660 --> 01:07:12,850
 Look-- look-- look, I'm not here to bargain, bozo.

1569
01:07:12,850 --> 01:07:14,650
Half a million, or you never see your Bunny again.

1570
01:07:14,650 --> 01:07:15,550
 Hold on, wait a minute.

1571
01:07:15,550 --> 01:07:17,710
How do I know--

1572
01:07:17,710 --> 01:07:21,250
how do I know you really have her?

1573
01:07:21,250 --> 01:07:22,580
 Archie, is this you?

1574
01:07:22,580 --> 01:07:24,690
 Oh, my god, it is you.

1575
01:07:24,690 --> 01:07:25,860
Are you OK, honey?

1576
01:07:25,860 --> 01:07:28,350
 My only daughter, and you had the wedding without me.

1577
01:07:28,350 --> 01:07:29,250
You are such a creep.

1578
01:07:29,250 --> 01:07:30,240
I don't believe it!

1579
01:07:30,240 --> 01:07:31,140
 Bunny, hold it!

1580
01:07:31,140 --> 01:07:33,090
We-- we didn't know that you were kidnapped!

1581
01:07:33,090 --> 01:07:34,630
We thought that you just--

1582
01:07:34,630 --> 01:07:35,880
well, that we thought that--

1583
01:07:35,880 --> 01:07:37,552
 Put my daughter on.

1584
01:07:41,520 --> 01:07:42,930
 Hello, Mom?

1585
01:07:42,930 --> 01:07:44,550
Mom, are you OK?

1586
01:07:44,550 --> 01:07:45,450
Oh.

1587
01:07:45,450 --> 01:07:47,220
Do you know where my Stones T-shirt is?

1588
01:07:47,220 --> 01:07:48,360
 Get off the phone, you jerk!

1589
01:07:48,360 --> 01:07:49,810
I'm gonna talk to Tanya.

1590
01:07:49,810 --> 01:07:51,143
 For god's sake, Bunny, you're supposed

1591
01:07:51,143 --> 01:07:52,650
to be scared and helpless.

1592
01:07:52,650 --> 01:07:53,694
 Hello, Mom?

1593
01:07:53,694 --> 01:07:55,630
 [CRYING] Are you getting married?

1594
01:07:55,630 --> 01:07:56,850
 We didn't know!

1595
01:07:56,850 --> 01:07:59,305
We thought you ran off with somebody.

1596
01:07:59,305 --> 01:08:00,380
This is awful.

1597
01:08:00,380 --> 01:08:01,280
What are we going to do?

1598
01:08:01,280 --> 01:08:02,940
What about my honeymoon?

1599
01:08:02,940 --> 01:08:04,320
 Go on your damn honeymoon.

1600
01:08:04,320 --> 01:08:05,240
See if I care.

1601
01:08:05,240 --> 01:08:08,890
 Mom, we've got plane reservations to Hawaii.

1602
01:08:08,890 --> 01:08:11,160
 If your father pays the money, I'll be home Monday.

1603
01:08:11,160 --> 01:08:13,480
So go, enjoy yourself.

1604
01:08:13,480 --> 01:08:15,500
What difference does it make?

1605
01:08:15,500 --> 01:08:16,680
 I promise we'll call.

1606
01:08:23,390 --> 01:08:25,729
 Hello, Archie?

1607
01:08:25,729 --> 01:08:27,149
You'll hear from me Monday noon.

1608
01:08:27,149 --> 01:08:29,641
No paying, no more Bunny.

1609
01:08:29,641 --> 01:08:31,876
